AGI -&nbsp;The gup Tiziana Gueli accepted the request for referral of the preliminary hearing submitted by the lawyers of Minister Daniela Santanchè in the proceedings in which he is accused of fraud against the Inps.> The next hearing was set at 20 May.&nbsp;
The judge granted the terms of defence to lawyer Salvatore Pino, who had taken over from yesterday to colleague Salvatore Sanzo. The lawyer asked for referral to be able to study the papers of the investigation he did not know.
&nbsp;
<div </div
<h2>Legal, from
"On the part of the pm there was a tenacious opposition because they felt that there were no conditions for referral but the judge decided wisely and, on the other hand, there was no reason to deny the petition." The lawyer Salvatore Pino, a new lawyer from Daniela Santanchè explained this.
"Ours was a simple request for referral, as there are in a thousand other processes in which the lawyer changes - Pino added -. No dilatory manoeuvre, I will assist the ministra and it is not excluded that it is heard in the classroom but I have to consider why the approach to the dossier has been recent".
"Inps will withdraw the constitution of civil part, it has taken note that there are no more pendences in place". Mr Salvatore Pino said so. The Prosecutor disputes alleged irregularities related to the integration fund for 13 employees, > during the Covid, by the company Visibilia> with damage to the social security institution. Pino has explained that the Inps> has been compensated with "something in more than 126 thousand euros" and that therefore will come out from the procedure and will no longer be civil part. "I heard yesterday the ministra and is very quiet" also said the lawyer who assists the defendant along with Nicolo' Pelanda, today absent for a legitimate impediment as committed in another process.&nbsp;
<h2> Long referral by prescription risk </h2>
In opposing a referral from them deemed "long", on May 20, Marina Gravina at Luigi Luzi underlined the "prescription risk" for some of the defendants challenged to Minister Daniela Santanchè in the preliminary hearing in which he is accused of aggravated fraud against the Inps. The prescription concerns charges that will be prescribed in seven and a half years, so in 2027, > because the facts date back to 2020. The debate in the Chamber was very technical, no reference to politics or possible dilatory maneuvers, only the fear, expressed by the representatives of the prosecution, that we cannot arrive at a definitive judgment for the prescription. Public prosecutors have brought examples in case-law on denials in similar cases. Judge Gueli explained that he had no other dates available for another hearing before 20 May. The other defendants are Dimitri Kunz and Paolo Giuseppe Concordia.
